keyValuePair.Value: What are you looking for from your team?
It's been a good pre-season for you. Do you think the team's ready for this first competitive game of the campaign? What can we expect from your boys?
We want to get into the habit of winning.
We're looking pretty good, I think. But this will be a step up in our preparations. We're ready and now I want us to get into the habit of winning games.
I'm looking for more of the same.
The players look in good shape. We know how we want to play our football and that won't change for this game. We're looking forward to it.
It's a big occasion.
Pre-season's one thing. This game is a step up when it comes to competitiveness. It's a big occasion and I'm looking forward to seeing how the boys handle it.
Is the team ready for a proper test?
You've had games to work on fitness and try out tactics in pre-season. This game is a first real competitive test. Are your boys ready for it? How do you think it will go?
I want to see real hunger from the team.
We've prepared well. The boys look in good shape. This game will have a real competitive edge, though. I want to see hunger and desire from my team.
I think we've got what we need.
I've been impressed with the lads in pre-season. We look fit and sharp. I think we're ready for this game now. Let's see how we handle the big occasion.
It's all about attitude.
We've been doing okay in pre-season and I'm looking forward to this contest. I want to see my boys at their best and handling the emotion of a big occasion.
Are you ready yet for this game?
Your team hasn't had the best of pre-seasons. Do you think your boys are ready for a game at this level? Or do you think it might have come too soon for them?
We're here to win.
Pre-season is about fitness and getting our tactics embedded in the team. I'm not worried about the results. This is a proper game, though. So now it matters that we win.
We've struggled for focus.
It's not been a great pre-season, that's true. We've not looked focused as a team. That all needs to change now. This is a proper game and I want to see us win it.
We're better when there's something at stake.
We've not been very impressive in pre-season. But I think we're ready for this game. We rise to the big occasion as a team. I'm confident we can win.
Can you win the %1s?
You've suffered the disappointment of missing out in the %1s. Are you confident your team can come back and put things right by winning the %2s?
This game's the only one that matters.
Look, that disappointment is in the past now. All that matters is the game that's in front of us. I've told the boys that and expect a performance from them.
We can't make the same mistakes.
I was very disappointed. We made too many basic errors and never looked right. It's absolutely essential that we put that right with a better performance in the next game now.
It's another step on the journey.
At this stage, I'm less worried about results and more worried about performances. The important thing is us developing as a team. This game's a great opportunity for us.
Are you ready to lift another trophy?
I guess you were happy to celebrate winning the %1s. Do you think your team's ready to follow that up with another victory and another trophy?
I want more going forward.
I think we're looking pretty solid and determined. That first win was pleasing. But I want to see much more from us as an attacking force. Let's try and put teams away.
Credit to the boys at the back.
That first game was a really good test for us defensively. It was always tight and we got the narrowest of wins in the end. All credit to the boys at the back. I hope they're ready to go again now.
It's about growing as a team.
I know fans want to see us win every game. That's natural. But, for me, the important thing is the quality of the performance. I want to see the boys continue to grow as a team.
